lace of sympathy in moral judgment, what it means to be humane, how to handle competing values, and the relationship between trust and democracy. For all those concerned with ethics, this book offers both new perspectives and resources for the ongoing consideration of how we should live.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aConfucian ethics. 0aReligious ethics. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Confucianism. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Eastern / General.2bisacsh1 aHarris, Eirik Lang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuang, Chun-chieh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIvanhoe, Philip J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIvanhoe, Philip J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLuo, Shirong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoetz, Heiner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTao, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTao, Julia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTiwald, Justin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYu, Kam-por, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYu, Kam-por, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZhang, Qianfan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438433165423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438433165/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Pres